Check_Vowel
Check if a Character is a Vowel or Consonant using Ternary & Logical Operators


Example I/0 :
Input: a      â†’ Output: Vowel  
Input: Z      â†’ Output: Consonant  
Input: e      â†’ Output: Vowel 
Sample Input
a
Sample Output
Vowel

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    char ch;
    scanf("%c", &ch);
    (ch == 'a' || ch=='e'||ch=='i'|| ch=='o'||ch=='u') ? printf("Vowel") : printf("Consonant");
}


